Describe an advertisement which introduced a product you have seen
- when and where you saw the advertisement
- what the product was
- how you liked the advertisement
- explain how you felt about it

One advertisement that really stood out to me was for Vinamilk, which is a well-known dairy brand in Vietnam. I saw it on TV during Tet last year, and it left quite a strong impression on me.

The advertisement promoted their organic milk product and was shown during a popular holiday program, so a lot of people probably saw it. What caught my attention was not only the product itself but also the way it was presented. The commercial featured animated cows dancing in green fields, along with cheerful music and colorful visuals, which made it very enjoyable to watch.

What I liked most about the advertisement was that it was both entertaining and informative. Instead of just focusing on selling the product, it also showed some scenes of their farms, where the cows are raised in clean and natural conditions. This made the product seem more reliable and trustworthy.

Another thing I appreciated was its warm and family-friendly atmosphere. It created a positive feeling and matched well with the image of a healthy dairy product. After watching it, I actually felt interested in trying the milk, and when I did, it lived up to my expectations.

Overall, I think it was a very effective advertisement because it was simple, engaging, and able to build trust with viewers.
